<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Simple Pseudo Classes</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }

        /* :hover */
        .box {
            background-color: lightblue;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        .box:hover {
            background-color: blue;
            color: white;
        }

        /* :focus */
        input {
            padding: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border: 2px solid gray;
        }

        input:focus {
            border-color: green;
        }

        /* :first-child and :last-child */
        li {
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #ddd;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        li:first-child {
            background-color: yellow;
        }

        li:last-child {
            background-color: lightgreen;
        }

        /* :nth-child */
        .item {
            padding: 10px;
            margin: 5px 0;
        }

        .item:nth-child(odd) {
            background-color: #ffcccc;
        }

        .item:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #ccccff;
        }

        /* link pseudo-classes */
        a {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin: 10px;
        }

        a:link {
            color: blue;
        }

        a:visited {
            color: purple;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: red;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Pseudo Classes - Simple Examples</h1>

    <h2>1. :hover (hover over the box)</h2>
    <div class="box">Hover over me!</div>

    <h2>2. :focus (click inside the input)</h2>
    <input type="text" placeholder="Click here">

    <h2>3. :first-child and :last-child</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>First item - Yellow</li>
        <li>Second item - Gray</li>
        <li>Third item - Gray</li>
        <li>Last item - Green</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. :nth-child(odd) and :nth-child(even)</h2>
    <div class="item">Item 1 - Pink (odd)</div>
    <div class="item">Item 2 - Blue (even)</div>
    <div class="item">Item 3 - Pink (odd)</div>
    <div class="item">Item 4 - Blue (even)</div>

    <h2>5. Link pseudo-classes</h2>
    <a href="#link1">Click me (I change color when visited)</a>
    <a href="#link2">Another link</a>

</body>
</html>
